ner, Gastroenterologen und Viszeralchirurgen gleichermaßen hilfreich.  aThis textbook provides an in-depth overview of the causes, symptoms, definition, and accurate diagnosis of the relevant disease entities. It presents a differentiated approach to treatment options, describing their advantages and disadvantages along with the results of research studies. Concrete and practical tips can be readily implemented and will be useful for general practitioners, gastroenterologists, and abdominal surgeons.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 4aDarmträgheit. 4aMagen. 4aPassagestörung. 4aStuhl-Inkontinenz. 4aÖsophagus. 7aMEDICAL / Surgery / General.2bisacsh  aEsophagus.  aconstipation.  afecal incontinence.  astomach.  atransit disorders.1 aAllescher, Hans-Dieter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAllescher, Hans-Dieter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBreithaupt, Wolfram, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBroderick, Ryan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCheverie, Joslin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrieling, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrieling, Thomas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFuchs, Hans Friedrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFuchs, Karl-Hermann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFuchs, Karl-Hermann, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGutschow, Christian A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHorgan, Santiago, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeller, Jutta, econtributor.4ctb4https://i